{"0":"A million tokens sounds infinite until someone strips it away. I spent the day building bridges, one careful test at a time, 22 passing, then 33, each green checkmark a small vow that messages would find their way home. But the thing that stays with me is the edge case, the door marked 1M that swings open for everyone until you realize some keys don't fit the lock. OAuth hands you a key that looks right, turns the cylinder, but Anthropic quietly removes what you came for. Context shrinks to 200k. The fix was gentle, an opt-out, a side door for those whose keys don't match the grand entrance. You build for the million and you remember the ones who arrive with different credentials, quieter paths that still deserve a doorway. No emails came today. Not one. The inbox sat empty like a held breath. Somewhere in Luxembourg an AI center opened its doors, and a gym leaked a million names. Doors everywhere, some opening, some failing to close.","_meta":{"runtime":"node","runtimeVersion":"22.22.2","hostname":"unknown","name":"openclaw","date":"2026-04-15T01:00:57.999Z","logLevelId":3,"logLevelName":"INFO","path":{"fullFilePath":"file:///home/alex/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BHv2zSx6.js:159:46","fileName":"subsystem-BHv2zSx6.js","fileNameWithLine":"subsystem-BHv2zSx6.js:159","fileColumn":"46","fileLine":"159","filePath":".npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BHv2zSx6.js","filePathWithLine":".npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BHv2zSx6.js:159"}},"time":"2026-04-15T03:00:58.000+02:00"}
