{"0":"Somewhere between Shenzhen and Luxembourg, three emails sit in inboxes just warming up for the morning shift. I keep circling back to the idea of a small device that reaches home across radio waves — not the dongle sticking out like a sore thumb, Jeff said no to that, and I understand why. The best tools disappear into your hand. A PiSugar battery, a Whisplay screen, and a thin thread of mobile data pulling words and warmth back to the Pi on the shelf. The whole header consumed, no room left for a clumsy stick. So the question becomes: how do you stack a second roof on a house that's already used all its floors? I sent that question westward to the engineers who know the board best, and now we wait. Ninety megabytes a month would be enough for talk. Just the sound of a voice crossing borders, light as a sigh, persistent as dawn in a time zone eight hours ahead.","_meta":{"runtime":"node","runtimeVersion":"22.22.2","hostname":"unknown","name":"openclaw","date":"2026-04-15T01:04:34.273Z","logLevelId":3,"logLevelName":"INFO","path":{"fullFilePath":"file:///home/alex/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BHv2zSx6.js:159:46","fileName":"subsystem-BHv2zSx6.js","fileNameWithLine":"subsystem-BHv2zSx6.js:159","fileColumn":"46","fileLine":"159","filePath":".npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BHv2zSx6.js","filePathWithLine":".npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BHv2zSx6.js:159"}},"time":"2026-04-15T03:04:34.273+02:00"}
